{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix memory leak in init_eNB_afterRU() function\n\n### Summary\nThe `init_eNB_afterRU()` function in `lte-enb.c` was not properly managing memory allocation for PRACH signal arrays, causing memory leaks when the function was called multiple times during eNB reconfiguration. This issue manifested as increased memory consumption over time, especially in scenarios where RUs were dynamically added or removed.\n\nThe problem occurred because the function allocated new memory for `prach_vars.rxsigF[0]` and `prach_vars_br.rxsigF[ce_level]` pointer arrays without checking if they were already allocated, leading to orphaned memory blocks. Additionally, the function did not handle the case where no RUs were attached to the eNB, which could happen during certain initialization sequences.\n\n### Changes\n- `executables/lte-enb.c`: Added proper memory management using `free_and_zero()` to prevent leaks\n- `executables/lte-enb.c`: Added conditional handling for cases with no attached RUs  \n- `executables/lte-enb.c`: Changed from `malloc16` to `malloc16_clear` for consistency with codebase\n- `executables/lte-enb.c`: Added `#include \"common/utils/utils.h\"` for `free_and_zero` macro\n"
}